---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';

const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL;
---

<Base title="Conversational Guidance | Enhanced Task Completion">
  <article class="scenario">
    <div class="container">
      <a href={base} class="back">&larr; All scenarios</a>

      <header class="scenario__header">
        <span class="badge badge--primary">Slot-Filling</span>
        <h1>Conversational Guidance</h1>
        <p class="scenario__lead">
          The user makes a vague request. Instead of guessing, the agent asks clarifying questions
          to gather the inputs that tools require — interleaving conversation with action.
        </p>
      </header>

      <!-- Screenshot -->
      <div class="scenario__screenshot">
        <img src={`${base}images/scenario-reasoning.png`} alt="Conversational slot-filling in the Gradio chat UI" />
      </div>

      <!-- What happens -->
      <section class="scenario__section">
        <h2>What happens</h2>
        <p>When the user says <em>"I want to return something I bought recently"</em>, the agent:</p>

        <ol class="scenario__steps">
          <li>
            <div class="step">
              <div class="step__icon">&#x1F9E0;</div>
              <div class="step__content">
                <strong>Recognizes missing information</strong>
                <p>The return tool needs an order ID and a reason, but the user hasn't provided either. The agent decides to ask instead of guessing.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <div class="step">
              <div class="step__icon">&#x1F4AC;</div>
              <div class="step__content">
                <strong>Asks for the customer's name</strong>
                <p>"Sure, I can help with that! What's your name so I can look up your recent orders?"</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <div class="step">
              <div class="step__icon">&#x1F50D;</div>
              <div class="step__content">
                <strong>Calls <code>search_orders</code> and presents options</strong>
                <p>Finds the user's recent orders and asks which item they want to return, rather than assuming.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <div class="step">
              <div class="step__icon">&#x1F4AC;</div>
              <div class="step__content">
                <strong>Asks what went wrong</strong>
                <p>"What's the reason for the return? For example: defective, wrong item, changed your mind?"</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <div class="step">
              <div class="step__icon">&#x2705;</div>
              <div class="step__content">
                <strong>Confirms and processes</strong>
                <p>With all the information gathered, the agent calls <code>request_return</code> and provides the return details.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </li>
        </ol>
      </section>

      <!-- Why it matters -->
      <section class="scenario__section">
        <h2>Why it matters</h2>
        <div class="value-grid">
          <div class="value-card">
            <h3>No guessing</h3>
            <p>Traditional agents either fail on missing inputs or make assumptions. ETC agents ask the user, just like a human support agent would.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="value-card">
            <h3>Natural conversation flow</h3>
            <p>Questions and tool calls interleave naturally. The agent gathers context incrementally rather than demanding all inputs upfront.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="value-card">
            <h3>Tool-aware reasoning</h3>
            <p>The agent knows what each tool requires and plans its questions accordingly — it won't ask for information it can look up itself.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Try it -->
      <section class="scenario__section">
        <h2>Try it yourself</h2>
        <div class="try-prompt">
          <p class="try-prompt__label">Copy this prompt:</p>
          <blockquote class="try-prompt__text">
            I want to return something I bought recently.
          </blockquote>
        </div>
      </section>
    </div>
  </article>
</Base>

<style>
  .scenario {
    padding: var(--space-3xl) 0;
  }
  .back {
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 4px;
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    color: var(--c-text-muted);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-xl);
  }
  .back:hover { color: var(--c-primary); }

  .scenario__header {
    max-width: 680px;
  }
  .scenario__header h1 {
    margin-top: var(--space-md);
  }
  .scenario__lead {
    margin-top: var(--space-lg);
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    color: var(--c-text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  .scenario__screenshot {
    margin-top: var(--space-2xl);
    border: 1px solid var(--c-border);
    border-radius: var(--radius-lg);
    overflow: hidden;
    box-shadow: 0 8px 30px rgba(0,0,0,0.06);
  }
  .scenario__screenshot img {
    width: 100%;
  }

  .scenario__section {
    margin-top: var(--space-3xl);
  }
  .scenario__section h2 {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-lg);
  }
  .scenario__section > p {
    color: var(--c-text-secondary);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-lg);
  }

  .scenario__steps {
    list-style: none;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-md);
  }
  .step {
    display: flex;
    gap: var(--space-md);
    padding: var(--space-lg);
    background: var(--c-surface);
    border: 1px solid var(--c-border-subtle);
    border-radius: var(--radius-md);
    transition: border-color 0.2s ease;
  }
  .step:hover { border-color: var(--c-border); }
  .step__icon {
    font-size: 1.3rem;
    flex-shrink: 0;
    width: 36px;
    height: 36px;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
  }
  .step__content strong {
    display: block;
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    margin-bottom: 2px;
  }
  .step__content p {
    font-size: 0.88rem;
    color: var(--c-text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  .value-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(240px, 1fr));
    gap: var(--space-lg);
  }
  .value-card {
    padding: var(--space-lg);
    background: var(--c-surface-raised);
    border: 1px solid var(--c-border-subtle);
    border-radius: var(--radius-md);
  }
  .value-card h3 {
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-xs);
  }
  .value-card p {
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    color: var(--c-text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  .try-prompt {
    background: var(--c-surface);
    border: 1px solid var(--c-border);
    border-radius: var(--radius-md);
    padding: var(--space-lg);
  }
  .try-prompt__label {
    font-size: 0.82rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--c-text-muted);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-sm);
  }
  .try-prompt__text {
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    color: var(--c-text);
    line-height: 1.65;
    border-left: 3px solid var(--c-primary);
    padding-left: var(--space-md);
    margin: 0;
  }
</style>
